<br>
In summary, I believe that Shelak, the power leveller, is the one that was truly malicious. I sincerely hope that his guild takes action against him. Perked is just a fool. Her main crime is stupidity.<br>
<br>
Here's what I believe happened:<br>
<br>
Perked and Shelak pulled two Mobs from a further room: one fighter and one caster <br>
For some reason they engaged them right next to our group <br>
<br>
Perked attacked the fighter while Shelak mezzed the caster <br>
While Perked and Shelak were attacking the fighter Mob, the mez wore off <br>
<br>
Since the caster Mob was closer to our group when the mez wore off, it aggroed on us <br>
It started casting and then charmed the wizard in our group<br>
<br>
Our wizard started attacking us, but the charm wore off quickly (or someone got off a cancel magic, but I dont see this spell cast in the log) <br>
<br>
Our Wizard said out loud (not to the group but to everyone) that the caster Gnoll attacked him and he was taking it down <br>
<br>
Our wizard blasted the caster gnoll HARD, as only wizards can <br>
<br>
I believe at this point Shelak REALIZED that his mez had worn off and re-mezzed the caster gnoll AFTER the Gnoll attacked us and our Wizard had engaged it<br>
<br>
I helped our Wizard take down the caster gnoll with a few dd's. The Gnoll Caster went down FAST <br>
<br>
Perked then threatened us with 'something BAD happening'<br>
<br>
Even though there were NO spawns around, Shelak and Perked started to say over and over again 'Please dont touch our Mobs' (or something like that). This was probably done to get that statement in the log for the GM's to see <br>
<br>
Shelak sat down near us (I would bet $100,000 that he was memming Fear) <br>
At this point Shelak probably petitioned the GM that we were KSing <br>
<br>
Two Gnolls popped right in our area and attacked us <br>
Symonn and I had our pets attack one of the Gnolls that had already attacked us<br>
 <br>
Perked and Shelak continued to say 'Please don't touch our Mobs' in order to get it in the log <br>
Shelak cast Fear on a Mob that NEVER touched him, but was engaged by both of our pets <br>
The Mob ran like hell further into the dungeon, followed by our pets, much too quickly and unexpectedly for me to back mine off<br>
This caused MANY Gnolls to aggro on our pets, eventually killing them <br>
<br>
The Gnolls that attacked our pets, then came back to kill Symonn and me <br>
There WERE A LOT OF THEM <br>
Symonn feigned death, while I got BADLY hit <br>
Our lovely Cleric healed me and Ator (thnaks Linitae!), who was taunting them off, causing them to aggro on her and eventually killing her I guess (I didnt actually see her die) <br>
<br>
After that things get fuzzy. I'm not sure if Shelak trained more on us, or if more Gnolls that aggroed on the pets came after the others due to bad pathing, or if Perked did indeed break the Mezzes of Yttria. I didnt see the mezz breaking, but the Fear thing is bad enough. It's really a clever way Shelak discovered to train someone and not get caught. <br>
<br>
That's my take on what happened. Take it for what you will.<br>
<br>
Artaud Tutuguri<br>
